# Next.js 15 App Router Patterns

## App Router Structure

- Use `app/` directory for all routes
- Dynamic routes with `[[...slug]]` for documentation pages
- Layout files for shared UI components
- Page files export default React components

## Route Handling

- [app/docs/[[...slug]]/page.tsx](mdc:app/docs/[[...slug]]/page.tsx) handles all documentation routes
- Use `generateStaticParams` for static generation
- Implement proper error boundaries and loading states

## Configuration

- [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) configures MDX support and PWA
- Use `@next/mdx` for MDX processing
- Configure page extensions for MDX files
- Set up proper build optimizations

## Performance Optimizations

- All pages are statically generated
- Use Next.js Image component for images
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Optimize bundle size with dynamic imports

## SEO and Metadata

- Generate sitemap in [app/sitemap.ts](mdc:app/sitemap.ts)
- Configure robots.txt in [app/robots.ts](mdc:app/robots.ts)
- Use proper meta tags and structured data
- Implement search functionality with FlexSearch

## PWA Features

- Service worker configuration in [public/sw.js](mdc:public/sw.js)
- Web app manifest for mobile installation
- Offline support and caching strategies
